&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Reliance Industries announced plans to construct a 3-gigawatt AI data center in Jamnagar, India, with an investment ranging from $20 to $30 billion. The facility will utilize renewable energy sources and NVIDIA chips, positioning India as a significant player in the global AI landscape. (&lt;a href="https://theaitrack.com/ai-news-january-2025-in-depth-and-concise/" target="_blank">theaitrack.com&lt;/a>)&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Artificial Intelligence News in December 2024 - AI Updates</title><link>https://dasarpai.github.io/news/artificial-intelligence-news-dec-2024/</link><pubDate>Tue, 31 Dec 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author><guid>https://dasarpai.github.io/news/artificial-intelligence-news-dec-2024/</guid><description>&lt;p>
